h origin): variant of   Maddox  ."]},{"name":"Maddux","meanings":["English (of Welsh origin): variant of   Maddox  ."]},{"name":"Mattocks","meanings":["English (of Welsh origin): variant of   Maddox  ."]},{"name":"Mattox","meanings":["English (of Welsh origin): variant of   Maddox  ."]}]},{"name":"Martha","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, of Aramaic rather than Hebrew origin, meaning ‘lady’. It was borne by the sister of Lazarus and Mary of Bethany (John 11:1). According to Luke 10:38, when Jesus visited the house of Mary and Martha, Mary sat at his feet, listening to him, while Martha ‘was cumbered about much serving’, so that she complained to Jesus, ‘Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left me to serve alone?’ For this reason, the name <i>Martha</i> has always been associated with hard domestic work, as opposed to the contemplative life."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":44,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":53,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":64,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":80,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":82,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Martha Maddox was born in 1505, in Kent, England as the daughter of Edward Maddox. She married Francis Stobaugh in 1530, in Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in August 1593, in her hometown, at the age of 88."},"et":{"1505–August 1593":"1505–august 1593","1505–1593":"1505–1593","1505–1550":"1505–1550","1530–1625":"1530–1625","1495–Male":"1495–Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1587":"1587","1530":"1530","August 1593":"august 1593","1585":"1585","1550":"1550","1495":"1495","1593":"1593","1505":"1505","1549":"1549","1625":"1625",", , Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Lympne, Folkestone and Hythe district, Kent, England":"Lympne, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1505–August 1593":"1505–elokuu 1593","1505–1593":"1505–1593","1505–1550":"1505–1550","1530–1625":"1530–1625","1495–Male":"1495–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1587":"1587","1530":"1530","August 1593":"elokuu 1593","1585":"15